Can't disagree with any of that (other than that I don't think PHP is necessarily conducive to creating truly beautiful code<i>). I think it goes the other way too: starting off with PHP doesn't give you a good idea of what other programming languages are like, and you'll find many things you grow accustomed to (or rely on) turned upside-down.<p>Maybe it's like learning to break the rules before you even know what they are?<p></i>* although to counter that, you can do some crazy things with it if you know how to. I abstracted Drupal's path finding method (drupal_get_path) into a magic static class. It's probably got a performance hit but it's bloody nice to look at:<p><pre><code>    Module::module_name('css', 'example.css');
    // vs.
    drupal_add_css(drupal_get_path('module, 'module_name').'/css/'.$file_name);</code></pre>
